Molten lava flows devastated forests and mountain meadows , creating a vast wasteland of mud , magma and ash .
The volcano holds a 600-foot ( 180-meter ) -deep glacier .
The crew aboard a helicopter taking measurements on Saturday reported the smell of rotten eggs , probably hydrogen sulfide emanating from magma .
Instruments aboard a helicopter sniff out gases seeping out of the rocks below and identify hot spots .
Global positioning system sensors detect outward bulges as slight as a fraction of an inch .
